text:
Dark Emblem from Ike's realm. 
Embodies a tyrant who plunged his 
world into turmoil.

Dark Emblem from Micaiah's realm. 
Embodies a goddess who subjected 
humankind to harsh judgment.

Known as the Emblem of the 
Academy. Wields various hero's 
relics and knows a variety of tactics.

Known as the Emblem of Echoes. 
Her holy magic is the bane of 
monsters.

Dark Emblem from Celica's realm. 
Embodies a conqueror who was 
consumed by bloodlust.

Known as the Emblem of the Sacred. 
Her flashing sword shatters her foe's 
defenses.

The Emblem contained within the 
Ring of the Instructor, which was 
stolen from Lythos Castle.

The Emblem contained within the 
Ring of the Sage Lord, which was 
stolen from Lythos Castle.

The Emblem contained within the 
Ring of the Lady of the Plains, 
which was entrusted to Elusia.

The Emblem contained within the 
Ring of the Princess Exalt, which 
was stolen from Lythos Castle.

Another Emblem of the Sacred. 
Pierces enemy lines with mighty 
lance techniques.

Dark Emblem from Eirika's realm. 
Embodies a being who corrupted 
others with foul demonic powers.

Dark Emblem from Lucina's realm. 
Embodies a Fell Dragon who 
wrought despair and ruin.

Dark Emblem from Corrin's realm. 
Embodies a spiteful dragon who led 
many to destruction.

Dark Emblem from Roy's realm. 
Embodies a dragon who tried to 
destroy humanity.

Known as the Emblem of Radiance. 
Destroys obstacles with his mighty 
sword and axe.

Known as the Emblem of Fates. 
Can tap into dragon veins, a magic 
sleeping in the land.

Known as the Emblem of Genealogy. 
A versatile knight proficient in axe, 
sword, and lance.

Known as the Emblem of Blazing. 
Defeats closeup foes with her sword 
and distant ones with her bow.

Dark Emblem from Sigurd's realm. 
Embodies a hateful god who struck 
terror into humans' hearts.

Known as the Emblem of Awakening. 
Creates bonds with allies, and pools 
their strength to attack enemies.

Known as the Fire Emblem. Grants 
the Divine Dragon's blessing and is 
the bane of the Fell Dragon.

Known as the Emblem of Beginnings. 
Reads enemy's intentions in battle 
and responds with a flurry of strikes.

Dark Emblem from Marth's realm. 
Embodies a mighty dragon who 
ruled through fear.

Known as the Emblem of Dawn. 
Supports allies with illuminating 
magic and a healing staff.

Dark Emblem from Byleth's realm. 
Embodies a king who massacred 
the children of a goddess.

Dark Emblem from Lyn's realm. 
Embodies a seeker of forbidden 
knowledge who brings calamity.

Known as the Emblem of Binding. 
Endures enemy attacks and cuts a 
path through with his sword.

Known as the Emblem of the Holy 
War. Boasts high movement and 
powerful lance attacks.

Dark Emblem from Leif's realm. 
Embodies a bishop devoted to a 
dark faith.

The staunch and loyal crown prince 
of Firene. He trains constantly to 
strengthen his constitution.

A traveling merchant from a wintry 
part of Elusia. She is a cheerful and 
cunning cheapskate.

An eagle found mainly in Brodia. 
Their mastery of air currents makes 
them adept at long-distance flight.

An opportunist using the chaos of 
war as cover to steal.

A rare animal found only in Solm. 
Royalty use these oasis-dwelling 
birds to send special messages.

A member of the Sentinels, and a 
chef with incredibly refined senses 
of taste and smell.

Prince Fogado's retainer. A young 
chef with a refined palate and keen 
sense of smell.

Prince Alfred's retainer. A tender- 
hearted man whose powerful build 
comes naturally.

A cat found only in Brodia. This 
region is known for cats with a mix 
of black and brown fur.

An ordinary soldier in the Brodian 
army.

Known as the Emblem of the 
Academy. A mercenary who 
became a teacher.

Known as the Emblem of Echoes. 
The princess of a vibrant country, 
as well as a warrior priestess.

The princess of Firene. Despite her 
gentle demeanor, she has an iron will 
when her people must be protected.

Princess Céline's retainer. A woman 
of noble birth who loves fairy tales 
and sampling folk food.

Prince Alcryst's retainer. Despite her 
fierce demeanor, she's a noble who 
cares deeply for her friends.

An apprentice Steward of the Dragon 
and the gentle twin brother of 
Framme.

The majestic crown prince of Brodia. 
His people trust him greatly for his 
strong, genuine demeanor.

This breed originated in eastern 
Elyos. Its appearance and behavior 
have adapted to its surroundings.

Known as the Emblem of the Sacred. 
A compassionate princess who takes 
up her sword for the sake of peace.

A dog found in all regions of Elyos. 
Known for their black coats, they are 
friendly and easily trained.

A dog found in all regions of Elyos. 
These friendly, intelligent animals are 
often kept indoors as pets.

Known for their characteristic fluffy 
coats, these sheep inhabit every 
region in Elyos.

A wild bird found in all regions of 
Elyos. At times they appear in large 
flocks, causing a spectacle.

A wild bird that inhabits coastlines 
all over Elyos. They constantly try to 
sneak fish from the day's catch.

A dog found in all regions of Elyos. 
Known for their white coats, they are 
friendly and easily trained.

One of the Four Hounds. A rugged, 
honest man who's loyal to a fault.

Daughter of the Fell Dragon. She is 
a brutal foe who seethes with 
oppressive malice.

Prince Alfred's retainer. A haughty 
woman with a love for building 
muscle.

The kind queen of Firene. A gentle 
soul who wishes for a world without 
strife or conflict.

A cat found only in Firene. This 
region is known for cats with black- 
and-white coats.

An ordinary soldier in the Firenese 
army.
A citizen of the Kingdom of Firene.

A freewheeling, optimistic young 
Sentinel. He's easygoing, but there's 
something mysterious about him.

The freewheeling, optimistic prince 
of Solm. More easygoing than one 
might expect of royalty.

An apprentice Steward of the Dragon 
and the determined, buoyant twin 
sister of Clanne.

Princess Hortensia's retainer. She 
seems demure on the surface, but 
is conceited to the core.

Fearsome member of the Four 
Hounds. A dangerously unstable and 
violent user of powerful magic.

An unidentified enemy. An evil aura 
radiates from this person.

A mischievous, spoiled princess of 
Elusia. She is nonetheless devoted to 
her family and friends.

The cunning king of Elusia. Worships 
the Fell Dragon and schemes for the 
advancement of his country.

Known as the Emblem of Radiance. 
A famous mercenary leader with 
unparalleled skill in battle.

A cat found only in Elusia. This 
region is known for cats with black 
markings.

An ordinary soldier in the Elusian 
army.

An owl found mainly in Elusia. They 
are strong and swift fliers, kept warm 
by their large feathers.

The mysterious, melancholy crown 
princess of Elusia. She never relaxes 
her icy royal decorum.

Prince Diamant's retainer. A warrior 
of few words who always keeps her 
wits about her.

A doctor's son from Firene who 
works his hardest to save all the 
lives he can.

Runs the only clinic in the village by 
the tea fields. Jean's father.

Princess Ivy's retainer. A handsome 
young man from outside Elusia who 
speaks freely and without inhibition.

Known as the Emblem of Fates. 
Someone with an iron will and the 
blood of the First Dragons.

A chicken found mainly in Firene. 
Despite their round shape, they can 
fly and sometimes carry messages.

Prince Alcryst's retainer. Her quiet 
modesty belies her superhuman 
strength.

Known as the Emblem of Genealogy. 
A brave prince in whose veins runs 
the blood of two crusaders.

Known as the Emblem of Blazing. 
A virtuoso swordswoman from a 
nomadic tribe that lived in nature.

A scholar from Elusia. Has a great 
hunger for knowledge, which he 
feeds with studies and experiments.

A rare animal found only in Elusia. 
Often found deep in the forest, their 
shed antlers make a wondrous cure.

Princess Céline's retainer. A smiling, 
refined gentleman who loves tea.

Known as the Emblem of Awakening. 
A royal heir who knows anything can 
change and will not yield to despair.

Successor to the Divine Dragon, 
awoken from a long sleep. Summons 
Emblems to lead the world to peace.

Veyle's Corrupted resurrection of the 
Divine Dragon. Summons Emblems 
by the power of the Fell Dragon.

The Divine Dragon, resurrected as 
the Fire Emblem. Has powers of an 
Emblem and the Divine Dragon.

A warrior fighting beside Emblems, 
on a journey of awakening.

The Divine Dragon and ruler of the 
holy land of Lythos. Vanquished the 
Fell Dragon 1,000 years ago.

The leader of a mysterious troop. 
Clearly devoted to her duty.

A general of Elusia. Commands 
Corrupted under his nation's flag.

A general of Elusia. Deployed to 
Firene to steal an Emblem Ring.

Boss of a band of thieves operating 
from a mountain stronghold. Has no 
morals where treasure is concerned.

Boss of a band of thieves and 
Totchie's older twin. Commands 
the Corrupted that haunt the oasis.

Boss of a band of thieves and 
Tetchie's younger twin. Commands 
the Corrupted that haunt the oasis.

A general of Elusia. Clearly devoted 
to her duty.

A rare animal found only in Firene. 
They prefer clean water and fresh 
produce. Legend says they are lucky.

One of the Four Hounds. 
A somewhat naive armored knight.

Known as the Emblem of Beginnings. 
A hero among heroes, brimming with 
nobility and charisma.

A guardian spirit that has lived on 
the Somniel since ancient times.

Formerly one of the Four Hounds. 
He is Veyle's knight, and has sworn 
to fight alongside .

Princess Timerra's retainer. She's a 
dashing woman with a fondness 
for animals.

Known as the Emblem of Dawn. 
Bearer of strange healing powers 
as well as visions of the future.

Hortensia under Zephia's control. 
Her consciousness is submerged and 
she is unaware of what is said to her.

Veyle, now crowned with the Fell 
Dragon's helmet. Her destructive 
urges and hatred are intensified.

The bubbly and outgoing crown 
princess of Solm. Known for being 
accessible and approachable by all.

The brave king of Brodia. A powerful 
and proud warrior, he prizes honor 
on the battlefield.

A corpse raised by the Fell Dragon's 
powers. It has no will of its own and 
exists only to follow orders.

A giant dragon raised by the Fell 
Dragon. Armored with tough scales 
and armed with powerful breath.

One of the Corrupted in a metallic 
form. Rare, but carries a lot of gold.

King Hyacinth, killed by the Fell 
Dragon. Turned into a powerful 
Corrupted by Veyle.

An elaborate Corruption of the dead 
Lumera, created by Sombron.

King Morion, sacrificed to resurrect 
the Fell Dragon. Turned into one of 
the Corrupted after death.

One of the Corrupted in a metallic 
form. Rare, but gives extra EXP.

Mysterious foreign troops who 
attacked without warning.

This breed originated in northern 
Elyos. Its appearance and behavior 
have adapted to its surroundings.

A member of the Sentinels. Though 
deeply religious, he loves to party 
more than just about anyone.

Prince Fogado's retainer. A fun- 
loving yet deeply religious cleric.

Princess Timerra's retainer. She has 
a tendency to speak in erratic and 
somewhat stilted tones.

A camel found mainly in Solm. Most 
Solmic households have at least one 
for transportation and carrying cargo.

The of 1,000 years 
past. Has no free will and obeys 
the Fell Dragon's commands.

A soulless soldier created by secret 
techniques. It has no will of its own 
and only follows its master's orders.

A soulless monster created by secret 
techniques. It has no will of its own 
and only follows its master's orders.

Long-eared rabbits that can be found 
hopping enthusiastically all over 
Elyos. Some varieties have white fur.

Princess Hortensia's retainer. 
He loves cute things and always 
maintains a bright, positive attitude.

Known as the Emblem of Binding. 
A nobleman who excels as a general, 
brave and intelligent.

A rare animal found only in Brodia. 
Considered a local guardian, they like 
uninhabited areas such as cliff tops.

The boss of a band of thieves in the 
borderlands who systematically rob 
every traveler who passes by.

A warrior from Brodia. She is a 
dauntless and determined seeker 
of truth.

A famous dancer of Solm. He is also 
a skilled fortune-teller and cultivates 
an aura of mystery.

The leader of the Four Hounds. She 
is descended from mage dragons 
and has lived thousands of years.

The free-spirited queen of Solm. 
Leads her country by example with 
heroic acts.

Known as the Emblem of the Holy 
War. A noble knight with a mighty 
lineage.

A cat found only in Solm. This region 
is known for cats with a leopard-like 
coat.

An ordinary soldier in the Solm 
army.
A citizen of the Queendom of Solm.

The Fell Dragon King. A wicked 
creature who wields immense dark 
power.

The Fell Dragon wielding the power 
of the Emblem Rings. Capable now 
of opening a gate to another world.

This breed originated in southern 
Elyos. Its appearance and behavior 
have adapted to its surroundings.

The self-torturing, wildly imaginative 
prince of Brodia. Has hidden talents 
even he isn't aware of.

One of a band of ruffians who have 
chosen destruction and pillaging as 
their livelihood.

Prince Diamant's retainer. Has a 
boundless enthusiasm for legends 
and adventure.

A Steward of the Dragon, long in the 
service of the Divine Dragon. He is a 
straight-laced, rigid gentleman.

Daughter of the Fell Dragon. She has 
overcome her dark personality and 
now fights for peace.

The younger sister of . 
Her darkness conquered, she fights 
for peace.

An illusion created with an engage 
skill.

This breed originated in western 
Elyos. Its appearance and behavior 
have adapted to its surroundings.

Long-eared rabbits that can be found 
hopping enthusiastically all over 
Elyos. Surprisingly, not all are white.

A thief encountered in a mountain 
settlement. She keeps a tight lid on 
the details of her past.

Princess Ivy's retainer. An enigmatic 
man who's always absorbed in 
intrigues of his own making.
